snippet.title: Lift Every Voice | Juneteenth
snippet.description:
Juneteenth commemorates the true end of slavery in the U.S. On June 19, 1865, Union soldiers brought news to Galveston, Texas, that enslaved people had been liberated -  over two years after the Emancipation Proclamation.

Today, we lift every voice and sing. Listen. Learn. Celebrate.

snippet.title: 155th Anniversary of Juneteenth Google Doodle
snippet.description:
Today’s video Google Doodle, illustrated by Los Angeles-based guest artist Loveis Wise and narrated by actor and activist LeVar Burton, honors the 155th anniversary of Juneteenth. Short for “June Nineteenth,” Juneteenth marks the true end of chattel slavery across the United States — which didn’t actually occur until 1865, two and a half years after the Emancipation Proclamation. Specifically, it marks the day when enslaved Black people in Galveston, Texas (one of the westernmost points in the Confederate South) finally received news of their liberation. 

Go behind-the-scenes of the Doodle: https://youtu.be/ipodBEnW9Hk
 
Learn more: http://www.google.com/doodles/155th-a...

To follow Google Doodles on YouTube, subscribe to: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCdq61m8s_48EhJ5OM_MCeGw?

snippet.title: Gender | ‘In My Personal Space’ Feat. Lily Cole, Sid & Dina | #CreatorsforChange
snippet.description:
From gender imbalances to the question of who pays the bill, Nadir tackles the subject of Gender with the help of Lily Cole, Sid & Dina.

As part of YouTube #CreatorsforChange, Nadir Nahdi invited some of the world’s biggest musicians, celebrities and fellow YouTubers into his wardrobe to discuss the awkward, uncomfortable issues we avoid in everyday life. The biggest of issues in the smallest of spaces.

Watch the other episodes in the playlist to see how Nadir and guests tackled hate with humour.

snippet.title: Chef May's Story: Rediscovering The Taste of Home
snippet.description: May became a celebrated chef in Manchester, England after learning to cook the flavors of her childhood in Thailand by watching YouTube. Find something new to learn at youtube.com/learning.
